    'telemetry.previewTitle': 'Telemetry payload preview',
    'hm.helpTip': 'Help',
    'hm.helpBody': '<h3>🎯 Overall flow</h3> <p>The Hunter is a discovery engine that opens up Telegram channels BEYOND those you currently follow. It works in 4 stages: <b>1. Internal mining</b> → <b>2. Web crawl</b> → <b>3. Telegram enrichment</b> → <b>4. Scoring</b>. Each stage feeds the next; no manual intervention needed.</p>  <h3>1. Internal mining (Stage 1)</h3> <p>Extracts candidate usernames from <b>your existing groups\' messages and links</b>: <code>t.me/{username}</code> URLs in the <code>links</code> table and <code>@username</code> mentions in <code>files.context</code>. <span class="hh-good">Fast · Free · No FloodWait risk</span>. Highest-quality source — fed by topics you already care about.</p>  <h3>2. Web crawl (Stage 2)</h3> <p>Visits public Telegram directories and search engines as a real browser. Doesn\'t use hardcoded URL patterns — visits each site\'s homepage, extracts category/listing links, walks sub-pages, harvests t.me references.</p>  <h4>Telegram directories</h4> <ul>   <li><span class="hh-tag">tgstat</span> Russia-based, the most comprehensive Telegram analytics platform</li>   <li><span class="hh-tag">lyzem</span> Telegram-specific search engine</li>   <li><span class="hh-tag">telemetrio</span> Public channel stats and rankings</li>   <li><span class="hh-tag">combot</span> Multi-language top listings</li>   <li><span class="hh-tag">tgsgg / tdirectory / tlgrm / telegramic / tgchannels</span> Various country/lang focused</li> </ul>  <h4>Search engines (Google dork syntax)</h4> <p>All issue queries in <code>site:t.me {keyword} {modifier}</code> format. Customize keywords in Settings → Hunter; if blank, 26 file categories × 3 modifiers produce 16 smart queries automatically.</p> <ul>   <li><span class="hh-tag">duckduckgo</span> <span class="hh-tag">brave</span> <span class="hh-tag">bing</span> <span class="hh-tag">mojeek</span> <span class="hh-tag">startpage</span> <span class="hh-tag">yandex</span> Scrape-friendly</li>   <li><span class="hh-tag">google</span> — <span class="hh-warn">aggressive CAPTCHA</span>; usually returns 0 and is parked for 6h</li> </ul>  <h4>Bot-evasion mechanisms</h4> <ul><li>Full Chrome headers · cookie jar · Brotli decode · Cloudflare/CAPTCHA detection · per-domain 6h cool-down on 3 fails</li></ul>  <h3>3. Telegram enrichment (Stage 3)</h3> <p>Validates and profiles each candidate via Telethon: <code>get_entity</code>, <code>GetFullChannelRequest</code> for member count, samples last N (default 200) document messages for type breakdown, computes score.</p>  <h4>ResolveUsername limit</h4> <p>This API has very tight limits. The first resolve caches <code>peer_id</code>+<code>access_hash</code>, and subsequent calls go through <code>InputPeerChannel</code> directly (limit-free). On limit hit, stage 3 enters <b>cached-only mode</b>: skips uncached candidates, processes cached ones, retries skipped tomorrow.</p>  <h3>4. Scoring</h3> <p><b>score = 100 × (0.45·density + 0.20·members + 0.20·recency + 0.15·diversity)</b></p>  <h3>🤝 What the program expects from you</h3> <ul>   <li>Set keywords in Settings → Hunter</li>   <li>Use multiple Telegram accounts (resolve limit is per-account)</li>   <li>Make decisions (Join/Reject/Blacklist) — don\'t pile up</li>   <li>Use Schedule (e.g. 24h) instead of clicking Run repeatedly</li> </ul>  <h3>📋 What you can expect from the program</h3> <ul>   <li>First run takes 5-10 minutes for ~100 candidates</li>   <li>Some Stage 2 sources may return 0 (Cloudflare-protected) — others continue</li>   <li>FloodWait pauses are normal; auto-retry happens</li>   <li>Rejected/blacklisted choices are permanent</li> </ul>  <h3>⚙️ Ideal conditions</h3> <ul>   <li>Stable internet · Multiple TG accounts · 5-15 personal keywords · Daily (not hourly) schedule · Habit of decision-making</li> </ul>  <h3>🚨 Common situations</h3> <ul>   <li><b>"Telegram username çözümleme limiti dolu"</b> → wait ~1-10h or switch account</li>   <li><b>"X kaynak cool-down\'da"</b> → auto-retry after 6h</li>   <li><b>"0 cache\'li, N resolve gerekli"</b> → Stage 3 trying to enrich new candidates; some may hit limit</li>   <li><b>Stage 2 slow</b> → normal; ~30 sec per source</li> </ul>',
    'hm.helpTitle': '🎯 Hunter — How does it work?',
